<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procumbens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea procumbens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in being glabrous in all parts and with solitary axillary flowers and similar shaped unequal sepals. However, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graminifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea graminifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the much smaller calyx and corolla, the wiry stems, and the sessile, filiform leaves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
